==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Godliness
<hw>God"li*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Godly</er>.]</ety>
<def>Careful observance of, or conformity to, the laws of God; the state
or quality of being godly; piety.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Godliness</qex> is profitable unto all things.</q> <rj><qau>1
Tim. iv. 8.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Godling</ent>⟦br⟧
